MovingObject - Class in p
This class represents a moving object over the land.
A moving object has a 3 dimensional position and a 3D velocity.
Moving objects are Comparable, which helps the right 3D rendering.
MovingObject() - Constructor for class p.MovingObject

R

registerObjectMark(MovingObject) - Method in class p.View
Registers a mark of a moving object.
Mark of a moving object can be like a bullet hitting the land, a rocket exploding into the land or a player crashing into the land.
Registering means displaying it somehow on the scene.
Implementation simply draws to the landscape.

ShapeObject - Class in p
Represents a(n moving) object which has a shape (which is not used in the game, for space matters we merged with its inheriter classes!).
The class also represents the rocket, if instances are created by callin the public constructor with false parameter.
The class also represents the player, if instances are created by callin the public constructor with true parameter.
ShapeObject(boolean) - Constructor for class p.ShapeObject
Creates a ShapeObject, a rocket.

statusLabel - Variable in class p.Controller
Status label for displaying messages.
step() - Method in class p.MovingObject
Steps the moving object.
Stepping a moving object means adding the velocity to the position and checking if it left the land.
step() - Method in class p.ShapeObject
Steps the object.
Stepping an shapeObject means not only adding the velocity to the position but also recalculating the points of its polygon.

View - Class in p
The view layer in the MVC architectrue.
The view consists of: 2 game scene parts, which is a view of the players and their environment including the land, 2 player status parts where we can see heights, our shield, and our weapon reloading status, one minimap of the whole land.
